section.p:
Queries are issued in the SDK using the query or n1qlQuery API (in
                some SDKs this is just called query). This API accepts a string
                which is the statement to execute, and returns the rows (or an iterable object which
                returns rows) representing the query’s result. Here is the above query, executed in
                Python:>>> for row in cb.n1ql_query('SELECT type FROM `travel-sample` LIMIT 4'):
...   print row
... 
{u'type': u'airline'}
{u'type': u'airline'}
{u'type': u'airline'}
{u'type': u'airport'}

The above query using
                cbq:cbq> SELECT type FROM `travel-sample` LIMIT 4;
